AWKA – A businessman, Mr Emeka Nwankwo and his wife Mrs Adaobi Nwankwo were on Wednesday arraigned at the Federal High Court sitting in Awka for allegedly manufacturing substandard aluminum roofing sheet. Nwankwo’s company, Great Meckon investment where he is managing director was accused of also selling the product which did not comply with the Nigerian Industrial Standards to the public. His company is based at the International Building Material Market, Ogidi in Anambra. The two count charges against them read: “that you engaged in the manufacturing of aluminum roofing sheet and did sell or deliver the said product for public consumption to the public without complying with the Nigerian Industrial Standards, thereby committing offence punishable under section 26(2)(i) of the SON Act 2015. “That the manufactured aluminum roofing sheet which fall below requisite and expected quality, thereby committed an offence punishable under section 1(18) (ii) of the miscellaneous offences Act, CAP M17 Laws of the Federation of Nigeria 2004,” it said. Counsel to SON J. O. Olofindare explained to journalists that staff of the organisation took samples of the product for laboratory testing and listed five witnesses that would testify against them. The accused pleaded guilty to the charges. P.I Chukwudebelu counsel to the accused prayed the court to grant them bail as they were husband and wife. Chukwudebelu said they were willing to stand trial and promised to produce them whenever the case would be heard. The prosecution did not object to the application for bail. In his ruling, Justice N.I Oweibo granted the couple bail for a sum of N1 million and a surety of not less than GL 8 in the civil service in the like sum. The matter was adjourned for May 24 for hearing. 0 comments